Solution:
The probability of getting exactly $k$ questions correct is $\binom{15}{k} \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)^{15}$.  Therefore, the probability of getting at least half the questions correct is \begin{align*}
\frac{\binom{15}{8}+\binom{15}{9}+\binom{15}{10}+\binom{15}{11}+\binom{15}{12}+\binom{15}{13}+\binom{15}{14}+\binom{15}{15}}{2^{15}}&=\frac{2^{15}-\binom{15}{0}-\binom{15}{1}-\binom{15}{2}-\binom{15}{3}-\binom{15}{4}-\binom{15}{5}-\binom{15}{6}-\binom{15}{7}}{2^{15}}\\
&=\frac{1}{2}-\frac{\binom{15}{7}}{2^{15}}\\
&=\boxed{\frac{6435}{32768}}.
\end{align*}
